properties.Name: Coating
properties.Description:
A coating associated with an apparel product.

Ex:
Coating:  A finishing process in which a substance - like rubber, resin or synthetic compounds - covers the fabric on one or both sides.  Polyurethane is a common coating for outerwear.  Coating typically aids water-resistance.

Urethane coated:  A thin layer of polyurethane is sprayed onto backside of fabric to waterproof, yet accommodates silkening.
